snippet.textDisplay:
You need to look into this man's childhood life on how he was raised. Apparently, his parents divorced when he was 10 years old. He grew up without a father which is basically the discipline and role model he's been missing. That explains his emotional reaction when he throws a fit, quite the opposite of what a "real" man or gentlemen would do. When you're raised by a single-parent especially a female in the worse circumstances (Poor-class or poverty). AB may have witnessed a lot of stress, anger, frustration and adopted that vibe. Top of that, assuming he's surrounded with the same issues in his neighborhood (aka Hood). This is a major problem in our black communities within the housing project or similar environment.


If this man grew up with both parents. I can certainly guarantee he would be a better person today than he is now. Unfortunately, you can't "force" to change a person's behavior or past. Only age will wear him down and that may take a while for AB...


I too had a similar past as AB. Very emotional that I would yell at my girlfriend the same things AB had said or maybe worse but it seem normal to me at that time. It took me years to recognize that issue and filter out most of my toxic behavior but my past remains as a scar. So the attitude is still there but not as worse. I'm still working on it and eventually AB will too.
